From 088e53724a93d8599a260cb34da00a2620dff30b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Slick <slick@slicksync.local>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 20:46:06 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: Watching for Xm now reflects real progress, not
 wall-clock time

Added startPosition to WatchSession (nullable, captured at session
creation from state.timeOffset/overallTimeWatched). durationSeconds
on the backend now computes as (current position - startPosition)
when position data is available, falling back to the previous
wall-clock calculation only when it isn't (older sessions, or an
item/provider that doesn't report a position).

Frontend now displays the matched session's durationSeconds directly
instead of an independent client-side (now - startTime) tick that
climbed every second regardless of whether the provider's position
had actually moved - confirmed with a real case where position stayed
frozen at the same value for 8+ minutes while the old counter kept
climbing anyway. Falls back to the previous estimate only when no
session row exists yet.

Also confirmed (not a bug, documented in the changelog): a title in
'Now Playing' but not yet in the 'Today' history grid is intentional
- Now Playing needs any nonzero progress, the history grid requires
5% of runtime.

Bump to 1.9.36, changelog entry added.
